  <h2 id="faq">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>

  <div class="space-y-6 my-8">
    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">How does Allianz's moratorium underwriting work?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        With moratorium underwriting, pre-existing conditions aren't covered initially. However, if you go 2 years without treatment for a condition, it can become covered. This offers a path to coverage that full medical underwriting (which may permanently exclude conditions) doesn't provide.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Does IMG's 50% deductible waiver apply to all care outside the US?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Yes, for most IMG Global plans, medical care received outside the United States has the deductible reduced by 50%. This applies to routine care, emergencies, hospitalization—any covered medical expense. Verify this feature on your specific plan, as terms can vary.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Can I switch between Allianz and IMG later?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Yes, but conditions that develop while insured with one company may be treated as pre-existing by the other. If you develop a chronic condition on IMG (which may not cover it) and try to switch to Allianz, that condition would be subject to Allianz's moratorium period. Consider your long-term health needs when choosing.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Which has better customer service?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        IMG Global has a higher Trustpilot rating (4.6 vs ~4.0), suggesting strong customer satisfaction despite lower prices. However, Allianz offers multilingual support in 15+ languages, which matters if you're not comfortable conducting insurance business in English. Both are reputable with established claims processes.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">What if I need care in the US with IMG?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        IMG Global covers US care, but the 50% deductible waiver doesn't apply. You'd pay your full deductible for US care. If you spend significant time in the US or have a high deductible, this could be expensive. The waiver is specifically designed to benefit expats living outside the US.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Are wellness checkups covered by both?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Allianz Care includes wellness programs and preventive care in most plans. IMG Global's preventive care coverage varies by plan tier and is generally more limited. If annual checkups and screenings matter to you, verify specific coverage before purchasing.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2 id="verdict">Our Verdict</h2>
  <p>
    This comparison comes down to what you're willing to trade for lower premiums.
  </p>

  <div class="bg-blue-50 border border-blue-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Allianz Care: Comprehensive with Strong Benefits</h3>
    <p class="text-neutral-700 mb-0">
      Allianz Care is the choice when mental health, maternity, or pre-existing conditions matter. Their €30,000 maternity benefit, comprehensive mental health coverage, and moratorium underwriting for pre-existing conditions justify the higher premiums for those who need these features. The 2M+ provider network and multilingual support add convenience, especially in Europe.
    </p>
  </div>

  <div class="bg-amber-50 border border-amber-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">IMG Global: Budget-Friendly with Smart Features</h3>
    <p class="text-neutral-700 mb-0">
      IMG Global is the choice when you're healthy, budget-conscious, and don't need extensive mental health or maternity coverage. Their 50% deductible waiver for international care and ultra-high deductible options create significant savings. The 4.6/5 Trustpilot rating proves they pay claims reliably despite lower prices. For healthy expats primarily living outside the US, IMG offers excellent value.
    </p>
  </div>

  <p>
    <strong>The honest question:</strong> "Do I need mental health coverage or might I have children while abroad?" If yes to either, Allianz Care's higher premiums are likely worth it. If you're healthy, don't need these benefits, and want to minimize costs, IMG Global delivers solid international health insurance at budget-friendly prices.
